    npm install @capacitor/core @capacitor/cli
    ```

3. **Initialize Capacitor**: Initialize Capacitor in your project.
    ```bash
    npx cap init
    ```

4. **Build Your React Project**: Build your React project to generate the production files.
    ```bash
    npm run build
    ```

5. **Add Android Platform**: Add the Android platform to your Capacitor project.
    ```bash
    npx cap add android
    ```

6. **Copy Web Assets**: Copy the built web assets into the native project.
    ```bash
    npx cap copy
    ```

7. **Open Android Studio**: Open the Android project in Android Studio.
    ```bash
    npx cap open android
    ```

8. **Run Your App**: From Android Studio, you can build and run your app on an emulator or a physical device.

